uiEntry.title: button_groupforms
uiEntry.tooltip: Toggle group formations panel||This panel can be used to arrange grouped units into different formations.||It has buttons for each formation, using different icons to represent infantry (crosses), cavalry (triangles), artillery (squares) and generals (stars).||To activate this button you must have some units already grouped.||Move your cursor over the formations panel for more details.

state.title: Inactive
state.tooltip: To activate this button you must have some units already grouped.

uiEntry.title: SingleLineStandard
uiEntry.tooltip: Single line standard||This is useful if you only have a few units to manage and will give you a wider firing area.||Units in a single line will be easier to break through if charged.

uiEntry.title: SingleLineCavalryLeftFlank
uiEntry.tooltip: Single line cavalry left flank||This formation can be used in attack or defence.||Use this formation to strengthen your left flank and use that flank to lead an attack.||If being attacked on the left flank use this formation to concentrate your cavalry there for defence.

uiEntry.title: SingleLineCavalryRightFlank
uiEntry.tooltip: Single line cavalry right flank||This can be used in attack or defence.||Use this formation to strengthen your right flank and use that flank to lead an attack.||If being attacked on the right flank use this formation to concentrate your cavalry there for defence.

uiEntry.title: DoubleLineStandard
uiEntry.tooltip: Double line standard||In this formation the infantry and artillery can support each other while the cavalry can be held in reserve to provide support in defence or sent in to attack the enemies flanks.

uiEntry.title: DoubleLineScreened
uiEntry.tooltip: Double line screened||The first line is used to look for hidden enemies ahead of the main group.||If you are ambushed then the first line will take most of the attack while your stronger units will be safe and ready to counter-attack.

uiEntry.title: TripleLineStandard
uiEntry.tooltip: Triple line standard||The first line is used to look out for hidden enemies.||If you are ambushed then the first line will take most of the attack while your stronger units will be safe and ready to counter-attack.

uiEntry.title: TripleLineIntegratedArtillery
uiEntry.tooltip: Triple line integrated artillery||This is a defensive formation as your infantry and artillery are arranged to support each other.||Artillery can not move with the same speed as other units, so using this formation to attack will leave vunerable holes for the enemy to exploit.

uiEntry.title: TripleLineGrandBattery
uiEntry.tooltip: Triple line grand battery||This formation can be used in attack or defence.||Grouping your artillery together means you can concentrate your barrage on one area of the enemy.||You can use this to destroy specific units or cover an advance.||Defensively it can be used to protect a weak area of your army, any enemies attempting an attack will be mown down.

uiEntry.title: ColumnInfantryVanguard
uiEntry.tooltip: Column infantry vanguard||This formation is useful to move units over bridges with a strong infantry line up front.||Having your units arranged in a long column can leave its flank vunerable to enemy attack.

uiEntry.title: button_withdraw
uiEntry.tooltip: Toggle withdraw||Use this to withdraw selected units temporarily from an encounter, or retreat from a battle to fight another day.||When using this your troops are simply withdrawing rather than routing, so clicking the button will stop the withdraw order.||You can also stop the withdraw order by giving them new orders.

uiEntry.title: UC_button_turn_left
uiEntry.tooltip: Turn left||Hold this button to rotate the selected units left, single click to rotate a small amount.||The final position will be shown using blue markers.

uiEntry.title: UC_button_move_forwards
uiEntry.tooltip: Move forwards||Hold this button to move the selected units forwards, single click to move forward a small amount.||The final position will be shown using blue markers.

uiEntry.title: UC_button_turn_right
uiEntry.tooltip: Turn right||Hold this button to rotate the selected unit right, single click to rotate a small amount.||The final position will be shown using blue markers.

uiEntry.title: UC_button_increase_rank
uiEntry.tooltip: Increase rank||Increases the rank, or width of the selected unit.

uiEntry.title: UC_button_move_backwards
uiEntry.tooltip: Move backwards||Hold this button to move the selected units backwards, single click to move backward a small amount.||The final position will be shown using blue markers.

uiEntry.title: UC_button_increase_file
uiEntry.tooltip: Increase file||Increases the file, or depth of the selected unit.
